MATCH_TOOL: Bash
MATCH_PATTERN: (^|[;&|(] *)npm run format($|[[:space:]])
ADVISORY: |
  `npm run format` runs Prettier across the ENTIRE monorepo (671+ files), not
  just files your feature branch touched. Running it in a feature branch
  produces massive unrelated churn that's nearly impossible to review and
  creates nasty rebase/merge conflicts.

  If you want to format only the files this branch changed, scope explicitly:

      # format only files touched since branching from main
      git diff --name-only main...HEAD | grep -E '\.(ts|tsx|js|jsx|md|json)$' \
        | xargs npx prettier --write

  If you already ran `npm run format` and got a monorepo-wide diff, revert
  the non-feature files:

      git diff --name-only main...HEAD > /tmp/feature.txt
      git ls-files -m | grep -v -F -f /tmp/feature.txt > /tmp/noop.txt
      cat /tmp/noop.txt | tr '\n' '\0' | xargs -0 git checkout --

  Real session cost (2026-04-18): ran `npm run format` expecting it to scope
  to my feature — got 671 files, 5831 insertions, 3021 deletions. Spent
  extra time scoping back manually before the feature PR was reviewable.
